dataloader <- function(x){
  if (x == 1){
  return(as.data.frame(read.csv("../data/same.csv")))
} else if (x == 2) {
  return(as.data.frame(read.csv("../data/diff.csv")))
} else if (data_to_load == 0){
  df_same = as.data.frame(read.csv("../data/same.csv"))
  df_diff = as.data.frame(read.csv("../data/diff.csv"))
  return(df_same, df_diff)
}
}

Load data

dataloader <- function(x){
  if (x == 1){
  return(as.data.frame(read.csv("../data/same.csv")))
} else if (x == 2) {
  return(as.data.frame(read.csv("../data/diff.csv")))
} else if (data_to_load == 0){
  df_same = as.data.frame(read.csv("../data/same.csv"))
  df_diff = as.data.frame(read.csv("../data/diff.csv"))
  return(df_same, df_diff)
}
}

Preprocessing

# make factors
if (data_to_load == 1 || data_to_load == 2){
  df$modality <- as.factor(df$modality)
} else if (data_to_load == 0){
  df_same$modality <- as.factor(df_same$modality)
  df_diff$modality <- as.factor(df_diff$modality)
}

# some quick calculations
if (data_to_load == 1 || data_to_load == 2){
delta <- df %>%
  group_by(trial, participant) %>%
  summarize(delta = RT[modality == "word"] - RT[modality == "image"], .groups = 'drop') %>%
  abs(.)

df <- df %>%
  left_join(delta, by = c("trial", "participant"))
} else if (data_to_load == 0){
  delta_same <- df_same %>%
  group_by(trial, participant) %>%
  summarize(delta = RT[modality == "word"] - RT[modality == "image"], .groups = 'drop') %>%
  abs(.)

df_same <- df_same %>%
  left_join(delta_same, by = c("trial", "participant"))

delta_diff <- df_diff %>%
  group_by(trial, participant) %>%
  summarize(delta_diff = RT[modality == "word"] - RT[modality == "image"], .groups = 'drop') %>%
  abs(.)

df_diff <- df_diff %>%
  left_join(delta_diff, by = c("trial", "participant"))
}

How variable are differences across trials?

# Fit linear-mixed effects model
model <- lmer(delta ~ trial + (1 | participant), data = df)
summary(model)

Our estimate for trial is very small, suggesting that there is minimal variablity in the differences (\(\Delta\)) across trials. This is visualized below

# df for pred values
new_data <- data.frame(trial = seq(min(df$trial), max(df$trial), by = 1))
new_data$predicted_delta <- predict(model, newdata = new_data, re.form = NA)
# Extract the slope from the model
slope <- fixef(model)["trial"]

p <- ggplot() +
  geom_point(data = df, aes(x = trial, y = delta, color = "Observed Data"), alpha = 0.2) +
  geom_line(data = new_data, aes(x = trial, y = predicted_delta, color = "Predicted Slope"), size = 1.2) +
  labs(title = paste("Observed Delta vs Predicted Slope (Slope =", round(slope, 5), ")"),
       x = "Trial",
       y = "Delta (RT Difference)",
       color = "Legend") +
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Observed Data" = "gray", "Predicted Slope" = "#22da4c"))  # Customize legend colors
